BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:12598d1d-9417-473d-8734-2e096c170c8a
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260409T000858Z
DTSTART:20260513T160000Z
DTEND:20260513T163000Z
SUMMARY:BayCare Presents - Mental Health vs. Mental Illness: Whats the Dif
 ference?
LOCATION:Tampa \, FL United States
DESCRIPTION:Mental health and mental illness are often used interchangeabl
 ybut theyre not the same. This presentation breaks down the differences\, 
 helping participants understand how mental wellness can exist even with a 
 diagnosis\, and how mental illness can impact daily life. Join us to explo
 re common misconceptions\, learn supportive language\, and discover ways t
 o promote mental well-being in our community. Click here to join the meeti
 ng (https:teams.microsoft.commeet25108891955457?p2Eq3JmmfO3nETNnJjA) \n\nP
 ermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/178701
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/178701
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1a4d7c94-de8e-44fc-92df-1d4ad66f2e0f
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260409T000858Z
DTSTART:20260514T160000Z
DTEND:20260514T164500Z
SUMMARY:BayCare Presents: Im Fine\, Its Fine\, Everythings Fine!
LOCATION:Tampa \, FL United States
DESCRIPTION:Saying Im fine can be short and sweet but doesnt usually give 
 an accurate description of our emotions. Sometimes we use\, Im fine to mas
 k feelings\, avoid conflict\, and pretend that everything is okay. This pr
 esentation will explore what it means to minimize\, ways we can acknowledg
 e and honor how we feel in the present moment and how we can take ownershi
 p of our emotions in the new year to navigate us to our authentic selves. 
 May 14\, 2026 Lisa Moser\, Psy.D 12-12:45 pm Register Here (https:events.t
 eams.microsoft.comevent88276a51-66e1-4ffe-ba0e-339dad737ce5599ceff3-02a8-4
 5bc-baef-c48cb8be94c4) \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/178246
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/178246
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:706a521f-723c-481b-b517-bb2cb2a248a9
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260409T000858Z
DTSTART:20260520T160000Z
DTEND:20260520T170000Z
SUMMARY:Webinar: Goal Setting and Motivation
LOCATION:Tampa \, FL United States
DESCRIPTION:Goal setting and motivation play a critical role in mental hea
 lth and emotional well-being. This seminar explores how clear\, realistic 
 goals can reduce stress\, increase self-efficacy\, and improve mood\, whil
 e unhelpful goal patterns can contribute to distress. Learn strategies for
  setting healthy goals\, maintaining motivation\, and supporting mental we
 llness in both personal and professional life. Presented by Bay Care and U
 HC Onsite Nurse Liaison. This webinar does count toward your wellness ince
 ntive benefit - 100  quarter. Registration : 5.20.26 Goal Setting and Moti
 vation (https:events.teams.microsoft.comeventb30dae4f-6f0f-492b-bb40-a8d74
 4e2dc56db05faca-c82a-4b9d-b9c5-0f64b6755421) \n\nPermalink: https://www.ta
 mpa.gov/node/185296
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/185296
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:4f91f4dd-c174-4c44-ac64-e16bfdb4fa2c
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260409T000858Z
DTSTART:20260527T160000Z
DTEND:20260527T170000Z
SUMMARY:Wednesday Wellness Webinar: Push Pause on People Pleasing
LOCATION:Tampa \, FL United States
DESCRIPTION:Respect and honesty are essential to positive relationships. H
 owever\, healthy boundaries that define appropriate physical and emotional
  limits are crucial for self-care and positive connections. Join this webi
 nar to learn how to identify and set healthy boundaries with your relation
 ships. This presentation does count towards your Wellness Incentive benefi
 ts - 100 Wednesday May 27\, 2026  12  1PM Click here to register or scan t
 he QR code \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/187481
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/187481
END:VEVENT
